  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nMy node is mining.\r\nbut the coinbase address(0x7097f41f1c1847d52407c629d0e0ae0fdd24fd58) is automatically changed in the middle.\r\n\r\nminer.setEtherbase(eth.accounts[0]) is not set\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: `1.7.3 or 1.8.6`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04.4 LTS\r\nCommit hash : develop`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Run geth\r\nnohup geth --datadir /sdata/ether/.ethereum \\\r\n--ethash.dagdir /sdata/ether/.ethash \\\r\n--etherbase '0x7a64ca9836b18fadaa52b2cbca3ca7d71edb6cd4' \\\r\n--unlock '0x7a64ca9836b18fadaa52b2cbca3ca7d71edb6cd4' \\\r\n--password /sdata/ether/account_pwd.txt \\\r\n--cache 4096 \\\r\n--verbosity 4 \\\r\n--mine --minerthreads=1 \\\r\n--rpc --rpcapi personal,db,eth,net,web3,miner,net,txpool \\\r\n--rpcport 6703 \\\r\n--port 6704 \\\r\n--rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 \\\r\n--rpccorsdomain '*' > /data/logs/geth/ether.log 2>&1 & echo $! > /sdata/ether/geth.pid\r\n\r\n2. Connect to geth\r\ngeth attach ipc:/sdata/ether/.ethereum/geth.ipc\r\n\r\n3. Check coinbase\r\n> eth.coinbase\r\nresult (the coinbase address is automatically changed in the middle) : 0x7097f41f1c1847d52407c629d0e0ae0fdd24fd58\r\n\r\n",
